<subSubSection box="[151,434,1453,1480]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,434,1453,1480]" box="[151,434,1453,1480]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,434,1453,1480]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,434,1453,1480]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName authority="AARVIK &amp; AGASSIZ" box="[151,291,1453,1479]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,291,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Conaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[306,434,1454,1480]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,866,1524,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,866,1524,1546]" box="[151,866,1524,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1525,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak, 2012" authorityName="Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak" authorityYear="2012" box="[294,862,1524,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Niphadophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albonigra">
<emphasis box="[294,555,1524,1546]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Niphadophylax albonigra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski" box="[561,862,1524,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" refString="Razowski, J. &amp; Wojtusiak, J. (2012) Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Nigeria. Acta zoologica cracoviensia, 55 (2), 59 - 130. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3409 / azc. 55 _ 2.59" type="journal article" year="2012">
Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak, 
<number box="[808,862,1524,1546]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="127" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1591,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1591,1616]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Description.</emphasis>
Head and Thorax: As in 
<taxonomicName box="[578,694,1592,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Neaspasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[578,694,1592,1615]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Neaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Abdomen: Male genitalia with socii well sclerotised, with row of strong spines on ventral edge; valva not strongly emarginate before cucullus, with one or two groups of strong spines on sacculus, cucullus spined in ventral part; phallus with internal folds, no cornuti. Female genitalia generally the same as in 
<taxonomicName box="[431,548,1701,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Neaspasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,548,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Neaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with two horn-shaped signa with broad bases, typical of that in numerous genera of Olethreutinae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="127" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1591,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1771,1796]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally 
<taxonomicName box="[466,598,1772,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[466,598,1772,1795]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Conaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closest to 
<taxonomicName box="[770,887,1773,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Neaspasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[770,887,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Neaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having a similar wing pattern, venation, and modifications of the hind wing and hind tibia in males. As in 
<taxonomicName box="[854,971,1808,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Neaspasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[854,971,1808,1831]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Neaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are abdominal depressions (dorsal pits) on tergum 
<quantity box="[328,371,1843,1868]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
both sexes. In males the hind wings tend to be shorter than in females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1591,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,442,1879,1904]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Systematic position.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[454,571,1880,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Neaspasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[454,571,1880,1903]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Neaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[636,769,1880,1903]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[636,769,1880,1903]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Conaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are considered sister genera. In addition to the external similarity and the structure of the female genitalia, the shared abdominal pits provide evidence of their relationship. Accordingly 
<taxonomicName box="[301,434,1952,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[301,434,1952,1975]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Conaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[444,523,1952,1976]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is placed in the 
<taxonomicName box="[723,860,1952,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Neopotamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[723,860,1952,1975]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Neopotamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski" box="[953,1304,1951,1976]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" refString="Razowski, J. &amp; Wojtusiak, J. (2012) Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Nigeria. Acta zoologica cracoviensia, 55 (2), 59 - 130. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3409 / azc. 55 _ 2.59" type="journal article" year="2012">
Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak (
<number box="[1237,1296,1952,1976]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak, 2012" authorityName="Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,752,1987,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sophrona" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,395,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">Conaspasia sophrona</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski" box="[409,744,1987,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" refString="Razowski, J. &amp; Wojtusiak, J. (2012) Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Nigeria. Acta zoologica cracoviensia, 55 (2), 59 - 130. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3409 / azc. 55 _ 2.59" type="journal article" year="2012">
Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak, 
<number box="[684,744,1988,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[763,862,1987,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="127">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, to belong to Neopotamiae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="128" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski" box="[325,675,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" refString="Razowski, J. &amp; Wojtusiak, J. (2012) Tortricidae (Lepidoptera) from Nigeria. Acta zoologica cracoviensia, 55 (2), 59 - 130. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3409 / azc. 55 _ 2.59" type="journal article" year="2012">
Razowski &amp; Wojtusiak (
<number box="[608,667,152,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
placed two of their new species, i.e., 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1231,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Niphadophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albonigra">
<emphasis box="[1121,1231,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">albonigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1292,1397,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sophrona">
<emphasis box="[1292,1397,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">sophrona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Diakonoff, 1992" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1992" box="[151,524,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Niphadophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Niphadophylax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Diakonoff" box="[332,524,188,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" refString="Diakonoff, A. (1992) Tortricidae from Madagascar. Part 2. Olethreutinae, 7 (Lepidoptera). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (new series), 28 (1), 37 - 71." type="journal article" year="1992">
Diakonoff, 
<number box="[465,524,188,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[721,856,188,213]" name="Madagascar" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Diakonoff" box="[874,1061,188,213]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" refString="Diakonoff, A. (1992) Tortricidae from Madagascar. Part 2. Olethreutinae, 7 (Lepidoptera). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (new series), 28 (1), 37 - 71." type="journal article" year="1992">
Diakonoff 
<number box="[1001,1061,188,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, both the female and male genitalia as described and figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Diakonoff" box="[630,826,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" refString="Diakonoff, A. (1992) Tortricidae from Madagascar. Part 2. Olethreutinae, 7 (Lepidoptera). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (new series), 28 (1), 37 - 71." type="journal article" year="1992">
Diakonoff (
<number box="[759,818,224,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
show that the three species placed here in 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1436,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conaspasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1304,1436,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Conaspasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authority="Diakonoff, 1992" authorityName="Diakonoff" authorityYear="1992" box="[421,907,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Niphadophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemicycla">
<emphasis box="[421,713,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">Niphadophylax hemicycla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Diakonoff" box="[720,907,260,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" refString="Diakonoff, A. (1992) Tortricidae from Madagascar. Part 2. Olethreutinae, 7 (Lepidoptera). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (new series), 28 (1), 37 - 71." type="journal article" year="1992">
Diakonoff, 
<number box="[848,907,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[960,1008,261,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="128">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
